r until he could sell both of them....<br><br><br>yet the level 59 warrior needed the rbg... so why did the casters roll?<br><br><br>I believe people think that casters dont get items, well i suppose they are right, they get SCROLLS... and casters want melee items to buy caster scrolls!<br><br>So why then, do melee's not roll on the 20-80k scrolls from emp. in seb? Because the casters yell and scream if they try....<br><br><br>soo this means:<br>If a melee person says its unfair for casters to roll on melee item, they are 'greedy' and 'wrong'<br>If a caster says its unfair for melee to roll on a caster item, they are 'right'<br><br><br>Said another way...<br>&quot;If a melee asks for any item more then 20k to be defaulted/nbg rolled, they are greedy, but a caster can get all their needed items and roll on melee's&quot;<br><br><br>basicly:<br>-RBG drops, group lotto<br>-Malo/Mala/Muzzle of Mardu/Mark of Karn/Visions of Granduer/Wind of Tishanian/Forlorn Deeds, defaulted if class there<br><br><br><br>Yes world is unfair, yadda yadda, but this is just wrong... its a game and CAN be corrected, but people choose not to speak up...<br><br><br>My obsevations, of the 6 RBG's drope din seb in groups i've been in + the one last night to my guildie...<br>2 clerics have won, 1 necro, 1 enchanter, 1 wizard.<br><br>the 6th one? In all my time in seb I've seen a rbg NBG lottoed ONCE, and the cleric gated with it and sold it before the GM worked on the case the day after.. so the caster was able to keep the cash, though i think he recieved a warning.. and the ranger didnt get the RBG she won.<br><br><br><br>Now to be fair to casters...<br>Yes melee's sometimes sell items and nbg for them again, but this is -far- less common from melee's(who depend on the items for ac/damage/etc), and is more common from casters who dont need(donals vambracers back a few months ago, FBCR, Runed Cowl, SMR), and some substitutes are cheaper at the loss of a few stat points/ac... So casters again are more heavily abusing NBG<br><br>I guess that wasnt to fair now was it? =/<br><br><br><br><br><br>Before i ask the question, I just want to say that I Myself believe NBG(in groups) is a joke, but some people cant always group with themselves using 2-3 computers, and sometimes cant always exp with guild groups at certain camps for items they need...<br><br><br><br><br>This question i ask is to try and help all the people who cant frequently do guild-only groups, and need to join groups, or want to join groups...<br>Should melee's stand up and fight back on casters more heavily? or should melee's start rolling on caster items? What can be done to NBG to stop the caster-abuse of it?<br><br><br>edit: names removed <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udiost.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DiosT</A> at: 3/6/02 1:43:06 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhyarth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hyarth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/6/02 11:20:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22643.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NBG....</span><hr size=1> Do what I do, make sure loot rules are absolutely clear upfront when you join.  If you don't agree, don't join.  If you do join, ninja every item that drops so you can enforce the rules.<br><br>--Hyarth has looted an RBG.--<br>Cleric says, &quot;omg!&quot;<br>Warrior says, &quot;wow, i need that.&quot;<br>Wizard says, &quot;ok, everybody roll.&quot;<br>Hyarth says, &quot;I don't think so, we agreed to NBG.  And because I looted it first, you don't have a say in the matter.&quot;<br><br>Problem solved.<br>/cackle <p><IMG SRC="http://www.personal.psu.edu/