pecting strangers to give you an item that they were a part of getting, simply because you can equip it. Or expecting to be able to roll for an item that you helped to get, with the intention of selling it to get an item you can use. I believe the first case is far more greedy.<br><br>And by all means, when a rare caster spell drops you should roll on it. Full random groups are just that Full random on droppable items. You all helped earn the items, you all should share in the spoils. <br><br>As far as the person who has one in the bank? Who cares if he has one in the bank, he still helped to earn it, so should be able to random on it like everyone else if he has someone there he can trust to hold it for him.<br><br>Nandail<br>55th Mage on Tunare<br><br>Rhumba <br>51st Sk on Tunare<br><br>Archy<br>52nd Chanter on Tunare <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uizualxev.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Izual Xev</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/6/02 2:22:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22643.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NBG....</span><hr size=1> whether i'm playing my wizard, cleric, or warrior.  any group i start is 1-1k roll on every item, if u dont like it, dont join.<br><br>when i join groups i ask them how they are doing loot, i dont mind NBG, but the fact is - caster loot isnt as common as melee loot.  If the 59 war wants a RBG maybe he should start a group and lay down the rules himself. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uizualxev.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Izual Xev</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.e